    <section>
      <h2>How We Tested These ACV Gummies</h2>

      <div class="tested-box">
        <h3>Our Testing Methodology</h3>
        <p>Our evaluation process was designed to go beyond marketing claims and assess whether each ACV gummy delivers real value. Here is exactly how we arrived at our recommendations:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Procurement:</strong> Every product was purchased at full retail price from Amazon, Walmart, Target, Whole Foods, or the brand's direct website. We accepted no free samples, sponsorships, or early-access products. Our editorial independence is non-negotiable.</li>
          <li><strong>Acetic Acid Estimation:</strong> Using published data on ACV concentration (5-6% acetic acid by volume), we estimated the actual acetic acid content per serving for each product and compared it against doses used in published clinical research.</li>
          <li><strong>Ingredient Verification:</strong> Each formula was cross-referenced against published clinical literature on PubMed. We evaluated whether additional ingredients (B vitamins, superfoods, probiotics) were present in meaningful doses or were included purely for label appeal.</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Testing:</strong> We verified all testing claims by checking certification databases (USP, NSF, USDA Organic) directly. Products claiming certifications without verifiable records were flagged.</li>
          <li><strong>6-Week Digestive Panel:</strong> A panel of 15 adults (ages 25-60) tested each product for six consecutive weeks, reporting digestive comfort, bloating frequency, appetite changes, and any side effects using standardized questionnaires.</li>
          <li><strong>Taste and Texture:</strong> Because compliance determines effectiveness, every product was scored on flavor, texture, vinegar aftertaste, and overall enjoyment on a 1-10 scale.</li>
          <li><strong>Value Calculation:</strong> Total cost was divided by the number of servings, weighted against ACV dosage and additional ingredient quality to determine true per-serving value.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Products were scored on a weighted scale: ACV Dosage (25%), Ingredient Quality (20%), Third-Party Testing (15%), Real-World Digestive Response (20%), Taste (10%), and Value (10%). The rankings above reflect these composite scores.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

